Tech Stack
MongoDB (database)
Express.js (backend framework)
React (frontend)
Node.js (server environment)
HTML, CSS, JavaScript

Additional Tools:

JWT (authentication)
bcrypt (password hashing)
Giphy API (for GIF search and embedding)
Focus

This will be an evenly focused full-stack application.

The backend will handle user authentication, note storage, and API routes
The frontend will allow users to create, edit, and manage notes in a clean interface
Type
Responsive web application
Accessible on desktop and mobile browsers
Goal

The goal of this project is to build a note-taking application that allows users to:

Create and store notes tied to their account
Access their notes from any device through login
Share notes with other users using different permission levels
Enhance notes using Markdown formatting
Add GIFs to notes to represent tone, mood, or emphasis

This project is designed to be a more flexible and expressive alternative to basic notes apps.

Users
Students taking notes
Individuals organizing tasks or lists
Users who want access to notes across multiple devices
Users who want simple collaboration without complex tools
Data

This project will use:

1. Custom-built API (Primary)

The backend will be built using Express and MongoDB to manage:

Users
Notes
Shared note access
2. External API

The app will integrate the Giphy API to:

Search for GIFs
Allow users to attach GIFs to notes
Data stored will include:
User account information (username, email, password)
Notes (title, content, formatting)
Shared permissions
GIF URLs attached to notes

-----Database Schema (Basic)
Users
    username
    email
    password (hashed)
Notes
    title
    content (text/markdown)
    owner (user id)
SharedNotes (/ permissions)
    note_id
    user_id
    permission (view or edit)
NoteGIFs (simple approach?)
    note_id
    gif_url


-------Authentication
User signup and login
Passwords hashed using bcrypt
JWT used for authentication
Potential Issues
Managing permissions for shared notes
Handling API requests to Giphy (rate limits or errors)
Ensuring notes save correctly with formatting
Avoiding overly complex features that slow development
Sensitive Information
User passwords will be securely hashed
Authentication handled using JWT
No financial or highly sensitive personal data will be stored

-----Core Functionality
User Accounts
Register
Login
Logout
Notes
Create notes
Edit notes
Delete notes
View notes
Sharing
Share notes with another user
Set permission (view or edit)
Markdown Support
Allow basic formatted text (headings, bold, lists)
GIF Integration
Search for GIFs using Giphy
Attach GIFs to notes
Use GIFs to represent tone (funny, serious, etc.)

----User Flow
User visits the site
User signs up or logs in
User creates a note
User edits note content (with optional formatting)
User optionally adds a GIF to the note
User can share the note with another user
Shared users can view or edit depending on permission
User logs out and can return later to access saved notes

------Stretch Goals (Optional)
Allow multiple GIFs per note
Add simple search/filter for notes
Improve UI styling
Add note categories or tags

------Breaking Down the Project (Tasks)
1. Design Database Schema
    Plan collections for users, notes, and sharing
2. Set Up Backend
    Create Express server
    Connect MongoDB
    Create API routes
3. User Authentication
    Register/login routes
    JWT implementation
4. Notes Functionality
    CRUD operations for notes
5. Sharing System
    Add/remove shared users
    Permission handling
6. Frontend Setup
    React app setup
    Connect to backend API
7. Markdown Rendering
    Display formatted note content
8. Giphy Integration
    Search and display GIFs
    Attach GIF to notes